WEBVTT

00:02.084 --> 00:03.879
I was unstoppable.

00:03.881 --> 00:05.241
I mean, I was...
I was on fire.

00:05.243 --> 00:08.933
It was like my mind and my body
were totally connected,

00:08.935 --> 00:12.568
like-like athletes must feel
when they're in the zone.

00:12.571 --> 00:15.931
Again, it was
miniature golf.

00:15.933 --> 00:18.489
Admit it, you're a
little turned on.

00:18.491 --> 00:20.520
You can't be this proud.

00:20.522 --> 00:21.961
Why not?

00:21.963 --> 00:25.923
Because I beat you.

00:25.925 --> 00:27.720
Hey.
Hi.

00:27.722 --> 00:29.089
Oh, good. You're back.

00:29.091 --> 00:33.527
We have some
exciting news.

00:33.529 --> 00:35.195
Okay.

00:35.197 --> 00:38.927
As you know, Amy and I have
been together a long time,

00:38.929 --> 00:40.757
and a lot of things

00:40.759 --> 00:44.717
I never thought possible
now seem possible.

00:44.719 --> 00:47.487
Okay...

00:47.489 --> 00:50.745
After a careful evaluation
of our relationship,

00:50.747 --> 00:55.846
we decided that the time was
right to take a step forward.

01:00.974 --> 01:03.733
Okay.

01:03.735 --> 01:05.664
Do you want to say it?

01:05.666 --> 01:08.735
Let's say
it together.

01:08.737 --> 01:12.035
We're getting a turtle!

01:14.066 --> 01:19.063
This is why I've been saying
we should keep champagne on ice.

01:19.065 --> 01:20.189
Sarcasm?

01:20.191 --> 01:21.459
Yes.
Okay.

01:21.461 --> 01:23.625
That was tricky,
'cause when it comes to alcohol,

01:23.627 --> 01:25.991
she generally means business.

01:25.993 --> 01:27.861
Well, we're-we're
very happy for you.

01:27.863 --> 01:29.029
Yes.

01:29.031 --> 01:30.294
Thank you.

01:30.296 --> 01:33.462
Acquiring a joint pet
is a big step for us.

01:33.464 --> 01:34.670
No. It's true.

01:34.672 --> 01:37.037
It means that we care so much
about each other,

01:37.039 --> 01:39.572
there's enough left over
for an eight-ounce reptile.

01:39.574 --> 01:41.476
Why a turtle?

01:41.478 --> 01:45.512
After much deliberation,
we've determined that a turtle

01:45.514 --> 01:46.713
is the ideal pet.

01:46.715 --> 01:50.213
They don't shed fur,
they don't make noise...

01:50.215 --> 01:52.250
For Halloween, we can dress him
as a cobblestone.

01:52.252 --> 01:53.252
Yeah.

01:54.282 --> 01:57.216
And if he ever goes berserk,
I know I can outrun him.

01:57.218 --> 02:01.917
Coincidentally, that's also
why I chose you as a roommate.

02:01.919 --> 02:03.084
Well, congratulations.

02:03.086 --> 02:05.155
Who would've thought
you two would be the first

02:05.157 --> 02:07.153
in our group to start a family?
Mm-hmm.

02:07.155 --> 02:10.453
That's what I said!

02:10.455 --> 02:14.092
♪ Our whole universe
was in a hot, dense state ♪

02:14.094 --> 02:17.426
♪ Then nearly 14 billion years
ago expansion started... Wait! ♪

02:17.428 --> 02:19.089
♪ The Earth began to cool ♪

02:19.091 --> 02:21.593
♪ The autotrophs began to drool,
Neanderthals developed tools ♪

02:21.595 --> 02:24.268
♪ We built the Wall ♪
♪<i> We built the pyramids</i> ♪

02:24.270 --> 02:26.935
♪ Math, Science, History,
unraveling the mystery ♪

02:26.937 --> 02:28.841
♪ That all started
with a big bang ♪

02:28.843 --> 02:29.834
♪<i> Bang!</i> ♪

02:29.835 --> 02:33.835
